==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coachwhip snake
<hw>Coach"whip` snake"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
large, slender, harmless snake of the southern United States
(<spn>Masticophis flagelliformis</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Its long and tapering tail has the scales so arranged
and colored as to give it a braided appearance, whence the
name.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coact</ent>⟦br⟧
